piece
Homonym Number: 2
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a piece (of bread and butter), snack
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: ca1920 G.L. Gabites, South Canterbury Applied also to a piece of apple etc ca1930 J.L.Kelly, West Coast. `Gis a piece, mum', the usual request for something to eat on return from school.
